<HEADLINE>
<P>
NCAA VOLLEYBALL / WEST REGIONAL; USC DEFEATS ARIZONA, MEETS STANFORD NEXT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By VICTOR CHI, SPECIAL TO THE TIMES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 USC left Arizona Coach David Rubio with a favorable impression as the Trojans 
swept his Wildcats out of the NCAA women's volleyball tournament Thursday 
night. 
</P>
<P>
 "If they pass that well, Stanford will lose," Rubio said. 
</P>
<P>
 USC advanced to the West Regional final with a 15-7, 15-9, 15-7 victory over 
Arizona and will face the host Cardinal tonight at 7. 
</P>
<P>
 Second-ranked Stanford (29-1) eliminated Arizona State, 15-8, 15-3, 15-6, 
behind junior Cary Wendell, who posted match highs of 14 kills and 30 assists. 
</P>
<P>
 "I've felt like we've been on a collision course with Stanford for a while," 
USC Coach Lisa Love said. "We're going to have to tie our digging shoes on 
tight." 
</P>
<P>
 Since 1984, USC is 9-2 against teams other than Stanford in the postseason but 
0-6 against the Cardinal. And playing Stanford, which beat USC in both 
regular-season matches, in Maples Pavilion is a daunting task. 
</P>
<P>
 "We've been an exceptional sideout team the last month," Love said. "A lot of 
it has to do with our passing." 
</P>
<P>
 Senior Meika Wagner led USC (.358 team hitting percentage) with 18 kills in 31 
attempts. Senior Lauri Yust added 13 kills and five blocks. 
</P>
<P>
 USC (22-7) jumped ahead, 6-0, in the second game, but Arizona (17-10) rallied 
to within two points three times. A block from Wagner and kills from Kilee 
Hughes and Vesna Dragicevic sealed the game. 
</P>
<P>
 USC opened a 6-0 lead in the third game, but allowed Arizona to even the 
score, 6-6, before coasting home. 
</P>
</TEXT>
