<HEADLINE>
<P>
UCLA WOMEN BEAT SAN DIEGO, 83-73 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Kisa Hughes recorded 17 points and a game-high 12 rebounds to lead UCLA to an 
83-73 victory over San Diego in front of 345 Thursday night at San Diego. 
</P>
<P>
 Nikki Hilbert and Kellie Bennett scored 15 points apiece for the Bruins (2-2). 
Zrinka Kristich scored 14 points. 
</P>
<P>
 Michele Brovelli scored a career-high 21 points for San Diego (1-4). Vicki de 
Jesus scored 13 points and Michol Murray added 12. 
</P>
<P>
 The Toreros, who trailed, 45-42, at halftime, pulled into a 63-63 tie on Laura 
King's basket with 8:05 to play. 
</P>
<P>
 However, UCLA took the lead for good on a layup by Hilbert with 7:47 
remaining. 
</P>
</TEXT>
