<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE TIMES MUSIC INDEX: COMPANY TOWN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 STACKING UP SALES 
</P>
<P>
 Total album and single sales of CDs and cassettes for the week ended Dec. 4, 
compared to week-ago and year-ago levels, in millions of units sold:  
</P>
<P>
 Latest week: Albums: 15.9 Singles: 1.8 
</P>
<P>
 Week-ago: Albums: 14.9 Singles: 2.0 
</P>
<P>
 Year-ago: Albums: 16.3 Singles: 2.4 Hits Magazine Tip of the Week 
</P>
<P>
 Signs of what Warner Bros. Records will look like under new Chariman and CEO 
Danny Goldberg are beginning to emerge, with speculation that current Warner 
Bros.Vice President of Product Management Steven Baker will be appointed to the 
presidency of Warner Bros. or its sister label, Reprise. Which label Baker will 
run is yet undecided. The major speculation revolves around who will run the 
other label. Goldberg is expected to make the announcement about Baker shortly 
after he assumes his new post in January. The other job is expected to remain 
open until a true candidate emerges. 
</P>
<P>
 Note: Hits magazine is a weekly music industry trade publication. 
</P>
<P>
 Source: Soundscan Inc. 
</P>
</TEXT>
