<HEADLINE>
<P>
SOUTHERN SECTION FOOTBALL PLAYOFFS; DIVISION V CHAMPIONSHIP; NEWPORT HARBOR VS. 
SERVITE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 RECORDS--Newport Harbor (13-0), Servite (11-2). 
</P>
<P>
 SITE--Orange Coast College, 7:30 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
 TV--Orange County NewsChannel, 7:30 p.m. Dimension Cable in South Orange 
County will show replays, the first being Monday at 8 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
 SERVITE--The Friars are playing in their first section championship game since 
1983, when they defeated La Puente Bishop Amat for their second consecutive 
championship. Servite's history includes the likes of NFL players Steve 
Beuerlein and Derek Brown. Servite's best running back this season is David 
Bedard, who rushed for 168 yards and three touchdowns to help propel the Friars 
beat El Toro, 34-19, in the semifinals. Bedard has rushed for 1,100 yards and 
scored 28 touchdowns. Frank Patti, who has 803 yards rushing, and Marvin Smith, 
who has 496 yards rushing and 12 touchdowns, complement Bedard in the 
backfield. Quarterback David Martin, who has completed 46% of his passes for 
990 yards, will try to keep Newport Harbor's defense honest. Martin has thrown 
10 touchdown passes with only six interceptions, and he will need to be 
mistake-free for the Friars to succeed. Tony McCanta is one of Servite's best 
defenders, leading a unit that posted three consecutive shutouts before last 
week's semifinal victory. 
</P>
<P>
 NEWPORT HARBOR--The Sailors, winningest team in the school's 64-year history 
of playing varsity football, are seeking the school's first section football 
championship. Comebacks and close games are their signature. Last week in 
overtime, it took a fourth-down one-yard touchdown run by Brian Johnson to give 
the Sailors a 13-10 victory over Foothill. Coach Jeff Brinkley led Newport 
Harbor to the Division IV title game in 1992, but Irvine won, 30-8. As 
sophomores, linebacker Dan McDonough and nose guard Bill Johns played in that 
game. Now, McDonough, who has 118 tackles, and Johns, who has 13 sacks, lead a 
defensive unit that has given up only 10 points per game. Johnson, who has 
rushed for 983 yards, and Edon Kagasoff and Jeremy Mason have combined for more 
than 1,900 yards rushing and 22 touchdowns. Quarterback John Giordani has 
completed 53% of his passes for 1,348 yards and 16 touchdowns with eight 
interceptions. An effective night from Giordani would prevent Servite from 
stuffing the run with an eight-man front. 
</P>
<P>
 KEY TO THE GAME--This game will be a physical, no-nonsense contest. Both teams 
have strong defenses and running games, so the passing game could be pivotal. 
</P>
<P>
 CONSENSUS--Pick tradition over destiny, the Friars will wear down the Sailors 
in a close one. 
</P>
<P>
