<HEADLINE>
<P>
TWO AREA RUNNERS IN CROSS-COUNTRY CHAMPIONSHIPS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MATT FARMER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The nation's finest high school cross-country runners will participate 
Saturday in the annual Foot Locker National Championships at Morley Field in 
San Diego. 
</P>
<P>
 Courtney Pugmire of Esperanza and Heather Garritson of Buena Park will compete 
for the West squad.Each of the four regional teams has 16 runners (eight boys 
and eight girls) who qualified at regional finals. 
</P>
<P>
 Pugmire, a senior who finished second at the State Division I finals and at 
the Orange County Championships, qualified by virtue of her fourth-place finish 
in last week's regional race in Fresno's Woodward Park. Garritson, a freshman 
and already the State Division III champion, qualified with a seventh-place 
finish. 
</P>
<P>
 Garritson's sister Carrie, a freshman at Alabama, was the first to qualify 
four consecutive years for the national championship race. MATT FARMER 
</P>
</TEXT>
