<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY COLLEGE ROUNDUP; CYPRESS' LATE RALLY BEATS MT. SAN ANTONIO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Cypress rallied from a six-point second-half deficit to beat Mt. San Antonio, 
68-62, in a quarterfinal of the Riverside men's basketball tournament Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
 Cypress went on a 14-2 run in the final 6 minutes 6 seconds. Jeff Cummins' 
driving layup with 1:30 left put the Chargers (9-2) ahead, 64-62. Gil Gonzales 
made four free throws in the final 15 seconds for Cypress. Gonzales scored 14 
of his game-high 21 in the second half for Cypress, which was behind at the 
half, 34-29. 
</P>
<P>
 Cypress plays in one semifinal at 7 tonight. 
</P>
<P>
 In another Riverside tournament game: 
</P>
<P>
 Imperial Valley 91, Fullerton 55 -- Marcus Austin scored 22 points for 
Fullerton (7-5) in consolation play. 
</P>
<P>
 In first round of the Los Angeles Valley women's basketball tournament: 
</P>
<P>
 Cypress 83, Sacramento 68 -- Sara Works had 35 points and 10 rebounds to lift 
Cypress (8-3) into the tournament semifinals. 
</P>
