<HEADLINE>
<P>
POP NOTES: BANDS BARTER TOYS FOR TUNES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Four local rock bands will play a benefit concert tonight at the San Clemente 
Elks Lodge to collect toys for underprivileged kids. 
</P>
<P>
 Performing, in order of appearance, are Loose Groove, Supernovice, Why? Things 
Burn and Pigmy Love Circus.To get in, bring a new, unwrapped toy valued at $5 
or more to be donated to the children's toy drive of the American Red Cross, 
Orange County Chapter. No cash will be accepted. 
</P>
<P>
 The show, open to those 21 and over, starts at 8 p.m. The Elks Lodge is at 
1505 N. El Camino Real. Information: (714) 498-7444. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Harry Belafonte will sing with his new band, Djoliba, Feb. 14 at 8 p.m. at the 
Orange County Performing Arts Center in Costa Mesa. The program will be a mix 
of old and new tunes with an emphasis on African rhythms and Third World 
themes. 
</P>
<P>
 Belafonte, who recorded his signature "Banana Boat Song (Day-O)" more than 25 
years ago and whose films include "Islands in the Sun," has received numerous 
awards for his human rights efforts including the Martin Luther King Peace 
Prize and the Nelson Mandela Courage Award. An Emmy-winning television 
producer, he is working on an ABC miniseries dramatizing the history of 
apartheid in South Africa. 
</P>
<P>
 Tickets to the concert, $26 to $46, go on sale Sunday at Ticketmaster outlets 
and the center box office. 
</P>
<P>
 Information: (714) 556-2121. 
</P>
