NATION IN BRIEF; GEORGIA; BODIES WASHED UP IN FLOOD ARE REBURIED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The unidentified remains of 97 people disinterred by floodwaters in July were 
reburied in Albany, Ga.The Flint River, swollen in July by more than two feet 
of rain in 24 hours from Tropical Storm Alberto, inundated two cemeteries. The 
cemeteries were heavily damaged, and 405 coffins popped out of the ground and 
floated downstream. Eventually 308 of the bodies were identified through 
various methods, but 97 people remained unknown. 
