<P>
CLU WOMEN GET RARE WIN AT AZUSA PACIFIC 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 For only the second time in 20 attempts, the Cal Lutheran women's basketball 
team came away from a trip to Azusa Pacific with a victory. 
</P>
<P>
 Sophomore center Evi Orolagas led the Regals (6-0) in a 75-66 come-from-behind 
victory Thursday, scoring six of her 14 points in the final four minutes to 
spark a 16-4 CLU run. 
</P>
<P>
 Orolagas sat out most of the second half after picking up her fourth foul less 
than four minutes into the quarter. 
</P>
<P>
 Nicole Albert had a team-high 17 points and five steals for the Regals. 
