<HEADLINE>
<P>
EXECUTIVE SUITE: COMPANY TOWN; THREE MOVE UP THE RANKS WITH HORROR FILMMAKER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Three executives have been promoted at the production firm of horror filmmaker 
Wes Craven. 
</P>
<P>
 Producer Marianne Maddalena was named president of Wes Craven Films.Jeff 
Fenner was named vice president of development, with Lisa Harrison named 
director of development. 
</P>
<P>
 Craven, who is currently filming "Vampire in Brooklyn" with Eddie Murphy, is 
best known for his "Nightmare on Elm Street." 
</P>
<P>
 * Priority Records appointed Paul Bishow director, artist development. 
</P>
<P>
 * Tele-Communications Inc. named Jedd Palmer vice president of TCI programming 
and president of Satellite Services Inc. 
</P>
<P>
 * Metro-Goldwyn-Mayer Inc. appointed David G. Johnson to executive vice 
president and general counsel. Ralph Wittenberg was named senior vice 
president, sales, for MGM/UA Home Entertainment. 
</P>
<P>
 * Nickelodeon has opened a new Los Angeles office, naming Robbie Rowe as vice 
president of development, Christopher Vaughn as director of talent relations 
and Paula Kaplan as director of communications. 
</P>
<P>
 * Lucy Wander-Perna was promoted to corporate senior vice president for Sony 
Pictures Entertainment. 
</P>
<P>
 * John D. Dumbacher was appointed vice president of licensing sales and retail 
for MCA/Universal Merchandising Inc. and Laura Jamet was promoted to manager of 
licensing sales. 
</P>
<P>
 * Ralph Walin was promoted to senior vice president of sales for Columbia 
TriStar Home Video, with Kimberle Lynch appointed senior vice president, 
overseeing legal affairs and distribution-related business affairs. 
</P>
<P>
 * Randy Parker is the new manager of international administration at Live 
International. 
</P>
