<P>
EAST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: MOORPARK; RATE HIKE APPROVED FOR TRASH COLLECTION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By SCOTT HADLY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Starting next year, Moorpark residents will pay slightly more to have their 
trash taken away. 
</P>
<P>
 The Moorpark City Council voted unanimously Wednesday to allow the city's two 
trash haulers to raise residential rates by 18 cents.With the new increase, the 
haulers, G.I. Rubbish and Anderson Rubbish, will charge $17.40 per month for 
their service, which includes recycling. 
</P>
<P>
 Seniors who now have reduced rates will also see an increase. Their rates will 
go up 14 cents to $14.10 a month. 
</P>
<P>
 "We've tried to shield residents from increases over the last two years,"said 
Councilman John Wozniak, who serves on the council's Solid Waste Committee. 
"This increase, though, is one that we felt was necessary to keep up with fuel 
costs and maintenance costs." 
</P>
<P>
 G.I. Rubbish hauls trash for about 60% of Moorpark's 7,000 customers, and 
Anderson Rubbish picks up the remainder. Both companies had also asked for 
increases of 28 cents to 49 cents for collecting recycled materials, but were 
denied that request. SCOTT HADLY 
</P>
