<HEADLINE>
<P>
EAST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: SIMI VALLEY; POLICE CATCH SUSPECTS AT BURGLARY SCENE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MACK REED 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Carrying stolen coins and jewelry, two would-be burglars left the Simi Valley 
house they were looting and walked into the waiting arms of several police 
officers, a police report said. 
</P>
<P>
 Devin Colwell, 18, and Benjamin Connell, 22, were held on suspicion of taking 
part in a midday burglary, according to Officer Vernon Trujillo's report. 
</P>
<P>
 A neighbor reported that a burglary was going on inside the house of Gary 
Kinoshita, 49, on the 2300 block of Collier Court on Wednesday, the report 
said. 
</P>
<P>
 Police officers and detectives took up posts around the house and grabbed the 
men when they left, the report said. Police reportedly found property stolen 
from the house. 
</P>
<P>
 Police also found that Connell -- who is a friend of a girl who lives at the 
house -- was holding a key to the house that he had no permission to use, Sgt. 
Archer Morgan said. 
</P>
<P>
 Police booked the two men at the East Valley Sheriff's Station in Thousand 
Oaks. The men were taken later to Ventura County Jail, where they were being 
held Thursday evening: Connell in lieu of $20,000 bond and Colwell without bond 
because of an outstanding warrant for defrauding an innkeeper, jail officials 
said. MACK REED 
</P>
</TEXT>
