<TEXT>
<P>
 British Firm Sues Bankers Trust: Bankers Trust New York Co. Inc., a big 
derivatives trader, has been hit with another lawsuit by a customer who alleges 
it was misled about the risks of the exotic securities.A subsidiary of Carlton 
Communications, a British media firm, charged in the suit that the bank's 
investment management division used deceptive practices when it traded in risky 
securities on Carlton's behalf. Carlton lost $4.4 million on the investments, 
according to a suit filed in October but first disclosed in Thursday's editions 
of the Wall Street Journal. The company seeks restitution plus expenses. 
Bankers Trust denied that it misled Carlton, saying the firm knew how its money 
was invested. 
</P>
