<TEXT>
<P>
 Toppled Toilet Draws Lawsuit: A woman who fell from a handicapped-accessible 
toilet at a McDonald's outlet in New York state is suing the restaurant's 
former owner for $600,000. Michelle Verdicchio and her husband, Louis, filed 
the suit this week in Saratoga County Court against Donald John Connelly, who 
owned the restaurant in Clifton Park, N.Y., about 15 miles north of 
Albany.According to the suit, Michelle Verdicchio was seated on the commode in 
June, 1993, when the toilet suddenly shifted and tipped to its side, causing 
her to lose her balance. Verdicchio, whose age was not disclosed, was thrown 
against the wall and suffered injuries to her right arm, shoulder, chest and 
breast, and she suffered emotional distress, the lawsuit said. It was not clear 
whether Verdicchio was using the stall because of a disability. 
</P>
