<HEADLINE>
<P>
TECHNO WATCH: THE GOODS; AN IMPROVED NEWTON HAS A MESSAGE FOR YOU 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By LYNN SIMROSS, SPECIAL TO THE TIMES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 For executives on the go, Apple Computer has introduced a more versatile 
version of its Newton technology, the Newton MessagePad 110. This lightweight 
compact device (1.28 pounds) not only organizes and categorizes information, it 
allows the user to take notes with a telescopic pen, then translates them into 
computer text that can be printed out later. It also has an infra-red beaming 
capacity, so information can be sent to others nearby using the Newton system. 
</P>
<P>
 With an additional External FAX Modem card ($220), MessagePad 110 can send 
faxes, receive E-mail and connect to on-line services. Newton Messaging Card 
($229) allows the device to act like a pager. 
</P>
<P>
 The MessagePad 110 has three times more memory than the original, longer 
battery life and a fast recharge feature. It contains a database for phone 
numbers, special dates and other lists, a dictionary of 13,000 words (names and 
other words can be added) and a "to do" list that will automatically transfer 
items not finished on a given day to the next day. 
</P>
<P>
 There are about 40 software titles that can be used with the MessagePad 110. 
The newest are Zagat Guide to Top U.S. Hotels and Restaurants (in 26 U.S. 
cities) and the Berlitz 5 Language Translator. 
</P>
<P>
 As a special promotion for its upgraded MessagePad 110 (suggested retail 
$599), Apple will include free a Newton Power Organizer Pack that's valued at 
about $250 until Dec. 31. Featured in the pack are the External Fax Modem, 
ExpensePlus to keep track of expenses while traveling, and Notion: the Newton 
List Manager with 100 ready-to-list templates, as well as a travel bag. 
</P>
<P>
 Newton MessagePad 110 is available at retailers nationwide. For a store in 
your area, call Apple at (800) 365-3690, Ext. 100. An Easy Way for Night Owls 
to Read in Bed 
</P>
<P>
 Like to read in bed? Then Nite-Owl, a high-tech book light, is for you. 
</P>
<P>
 Developed by Lumatec Industries of Austin, Tex., NiteOwl is lightweight (2 
ounces) and has a reflector lamp that provides a glare-free white light 
directly on the page. A retractable neck allows the reader to slide the lamp to 
the desired height for reading and the adjustable head can be positioned 
properly for both hardcover and paperback books. 
</P>
<P>
 NiteOwl (suggested retail, $25-$30) is cordless (it takes two AA batteries), 
has an automatic switch (when you move the neck in place to read, it switches 
on) and anti-slip pads so it stays on the book. It can even double as a 
bookmark.  
</P>
<P>
 An A/C adapter kit ($15) is also available if you want to plug Nite-Owl into 
an electrical outlet at home and save the batteries for traveling. 
</P>
<P>
 NiteOwl can be purchased at Sharper Image stores or through its catalogue, 
(800) 344-4444, from Brookstone, (800) 926-7000, or from Lumatec, (800) 
776-7945. Get Those Stains (and Smells) Out 
</P>
<P>
 Sherry's Miracle II is a new liquid stain remover and odor dissolver that 
neutralizes odors on carpet, upholstery or wood floors by using bacteria and 
enzymes to rid the affected area of smells. 
</P>
<P>
 Biodegradable and solvent free, it seems especially effective on pet odors and 
stains on carpet and upholstery, but also removes a variety of stains, 
including crayon, grass, blood, coffee and tea. 
</P>
<P>
 To order, send a check to Sherry's Miracle, 12115 Magnolia Blvd., North 
Hollywood, Calif. 91607. Or, in California, call (800) 774-3779. Sherry's 
Miracle II comes in several sizes: one pint ($10); two ($20); three ($29); four 
($36); five ($45); six ($54). Add $2.50 for shipping and handling. 
</P>
