METROPOLITAN DIGEST / LOS ANGELES COUNTY NEWS IN BRIEF: VAN NUYS; MAN PLEADS 
NOT GUILTY TO PAINTING GRAFFITI AT 200 SITES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 An accused tagger pleaded not guilty Thursday to a rare felony vandalism 
charge filed against an adult for allegedly scrawling graffiti on 200 North 
Hollywood sites over a six-month period, according to the district attorney's 
office. 
</P>
<P>
 Jaime Anthony Rodriguez, 20, of North Hollywood, is accused of spraying or 
marking his moniker, James 129, on scores of walls, street signs, curbs, street 
lights and billboards between May 3 and Nov. 29, causing more than $12,000 in 
damage, according to Deputy Dist. Atty. Mitchel Harris. 
</P>
<P>
 Rodriguez's case is probably the first where prosecutors reached the felony 
level in an adult case by adding up the cost of erasing the hundreds of tags, 
said Sandi Gibbons, spokeswoman for the district attorney. 
</P>
