</P>
<P>
 HUNTINGTON BEACH Service Groups Fund Crime Fighting Who: Rotary Club and Elks 
Lodge 
</P>
<P>
 Contribution: Donated money to the Huntington Beach Police Department to help 
fight crime. The Rotary Club recently donated $250 to help the Police 
Department cross-train one of its police dogs for weapons detection. The Elks 
Lodge has also donated $1,000 to the department's DARE unit. Officials said the 
donations are especially appreciated because of the city's tight financial 
situation. 
</P>
