<HEADLINE>
<P>
EAST VALLEY FOCUS: PACOIMA; YAROSLAVSKY TO HEAD CHRISTMAS PARADE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By TIM MAY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Newly elected Los Angeles County Supervisor Zev Yaroslavsky, a former city 
councilman, will don yet another hat Saturday, when he serves as grand marshal 
of Pacoima's annual Christmas parade. 
</P>
<P>
 Yaroslavsky, who had represented Los Angeles' 5th Council District, won his 
recent bid to succeed Supervisor Ed Edelman and now represents Pacoima and the 
rest of the 3rd Supervisorial District.The 3rd district covers most of the San 
Fernando Valley.  
</P>
<P>
 Also scheduled to participate in the parade are Diane Diaz of KNBC News and 
Kim Fields, a star of the television show "Living Single." 
</P>
<P>
 The parade will feature floats, drill teams, dancers and marching bands from 
area high schools, and kicks off at 10 a.m. at TransWorld Bank, 13657 Van Nuys 
Blvd. The parade will proceed down Van Nuys Boulevard to Glenoaks Boulevard and 
end with a party at the Boys & Girls Club of the San Fernando Valley, 11251 
Glenoaks Blvd. 
</P>
<P>
 One of the floats in the parade will be built by volunteers from Phoenix 
Academy in Lake View Terrace, a residential drug treatment center for 
teen-agers, and youth from the Pacoima Community Youth Cultural Center. The 
float features the theme: "Pacoima United." TIM MAY 
</P>
</TEXT>
