</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By FRANK MESSINA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Olive Crest is looking for a wide range of donations -- from appliances to 
Christmas toys. 
</P>
<P>
 The nonprofit organization has 13 group homes in Orange County that try to 
create a family environment for physically and sexually abused children who 
have been taken from their parents by the courts. 
</P>
<P>
 Olive Crest finds houses in neighborhoods that become homes for six children 
from preschoolers through age 18. 
</P>
<P>
 "Unfortunately, Christmas is a time when our children are most painfully aware 
of what they do not have and what other children do have," said Darryl 
Anderson, chairman of the Olive Crest board of directors. "We strive to make 
them feel valued, loved and cared for, especially during this time of year." 
</P>
<P>
 Because the homes need constant upkeep and essential household goods need to 
be replaced, group home officials said, requests on their holiday wish list 
include furniture, major appliances, televisions, VCRs, vacuum cleaners, 
kitchen goods and other household items. 
</P>
<P>
 For more information about Olive Crest programs or to make a donation, call 
Julie Seaborn at (714) 543-KIDS, Ext. 144. FRANK MESSINA 
