<P>
ARAFAT'S WIFE EXPECTING CHILD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Yasser Arafat is going to be a father. His wife, Suha, announced her pregnancy 
in an interview with Israel Radio's Arabic-language service.She is 1 1/2 months 
pregnant. 
</P>
<P>
 Arafat, 65, who leaves for Norway today to receive the Nobel Peace Prize, got 
the news Wednesday night. 
</P>
<P>
 "The timing is good. It will be the child of peace," said Suha Arafat, 31, who 
married the Palestinian leader in 1991. 
</P>
<P>
 It will be the couple's first biological child. They also care for 38 war 
orphans Arafat brought out of Palestinian refugee camps. 
</P>
