<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY IN BANKRUPTCY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Relative Worth 
</P>
<P>
 How much is $1.5 billion? 
</P>
<P>
 More than $1,000 for each county taxpayer 
</P>
<P>
 Laid end to end, 1.5 billion dollar bills would circle the earth almost six 
times at the equator 
</P>
<P>
 How does the $1.5 billion loss compare to other disasters? 
</P>
<P>
 Oakland firestorm, 1991: $1.7 billion* 
</P>
<P>
 Loma Prieta earthquake, 1989: $960 million* 
</P>
<P>
 Southern California wildfires, 1993: $950 million* 
</P>
<P>
 Los Angeles riots, 1992: $775 million* 
</P>
<P>
 What would $1.5 billion buy? 
</P>
<P>
 One and a half Foothill tollways or one and half San Joaquin Hills tollways 
</P>
<P>
 Twenty-four Thomas F. Riley Terminals at John Wayne Airport 
</P>
<P>
 About 12 Anaheim Ponds 
</P>
<P>
 Two Disneyland expansions 
</P>
<P>
 Nearly 80% of the Interstate 5 Widening Project 
</P>
<P>
 *Insured losses 
</P>
<P>
 Source: Property Claims Sevices (American Insurance Services Group), Times 
reports; Researched by SHEILA A. KERN / Los Angeles Times 
</P>
