<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: FULLERTON; YOUNG CYCLISTS CAN GET $10 HELMET DISCOUNTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MIMI KO 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 In an effort to get bicyclists younger than 18 to wear helmets, the Police 
Department and two local bicycle shops are offering $10 discount coupons for 
the headgear. 
</P>
<P>
 Police passed out the coupons at schools throughout the city to encourage 
parents to buy the helmets for their children.Beginning Jan. 1, police said, 
they will cite any youngster riding a bicycle without a helmet. The citation 
will carry a fine that has yet to be set by the courts. 
</P>
<P>
 The average price of a helmet is $20, and the shops offering the $10 discounts 
are JAX Bicycle Center, 2520 E. Chapman Ave., and Mulrooney's Fullerton 
Bicycle, 424 E. Commonwealth Ave. 
</P>
<P>
 State law requires bicycle riders or passengers younger than 18 to wear 
helmets approved by the U.S. Department of Transportation. The law took effect 
last Jan. 1 but local police have not issued tickets. 
</P>
<P>
 Approved helmets have a stickers with "DOT," "ANSI" or "SNELL" written on 
them, authorities said. For more information about the bicycle helmet law, call 
the Police Department at (714) 738-3153.MIMI KO 
</P>
</TEXT>
