<BYLINE>
<P>
By RUSS LOAR 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The school board agreed Tuesday night to wait until January to decide whether 
to appoint a new superintendent from candidates within the district or launch 
an outside search. 
</P>
<P>
 The illness of one Irvine Unified School District trustee forced the board to 
cancel interviews with two Irvine deputy superintendents, both candidates for 
the job. 
</P>
<P>
 The board has scheduled a special meeting for Monday to discuss the 
replacement of former Supt. David E. Brown, who left in October to head the 
Napa Valley Unified School District. 
</P>
<P>
 Brown joined the school district in 1988, replacing founding Irvine Unified 
Supt. A. Stanley Corey. Deputy Supt. Susan Long and Paul Reed are candidates 
for the district's top job. 
</P>
<P>
 The school board has meetings scheduled for Jan. 3 and 17, but trustees have 
not decided at which meeting a decision will be made. 
</P>
<P>
 The special meeting Monday will begin at 5:30 p.m. with a public discussion of 
the possible effects of the county's investment losses on the school district. 
