<HEADLINE>
<P>
BODY OF WOMAN FOUND IN VEHICLE LEFT AT IRVINE HOSPITAL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By THAO HUA, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A woman was found shot to death Thursday in a vehicle abandoned at the 
emergency room entrance of the Irvine Medical Center, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 A hospital security guard discovered the victim, who appeared to be in her 
40s, under a pile of blankets and clothes in the passenger seat of a Toyota 
Landcruiser about 11:30 a.m., Irvine Police Lt. Sam Allevato said.She had been 
shot in the head. 
</P>
<P>
 Witnesses told police a man in his 30s drove the vehicle to the back of the 
hospital, opened the door and walked away with the engine running, Allevato 
said. The man was last seen leaving the parking lot and heading toward Alton 
Parkway. 
</P>
<P>
 An hourlong search using a police helicopter and bloodhounds failed to locate 
the man, authorities said. Police found footprints that ended at Alton Parkway 
and Laguna Canyon Road, Allevato said. 
</P>
<P>
 "We trailed the suspect as far as we could," he said. "We think he may have 
hitchhiked." 
</P>
<P>
 Investigators described the suspect as a bespectacled white man, about six 
feet tall with brown hair. He was wearing a brown shirt and gray pants. 
</P>
<P>
 The vehicle was registered to an address in Huntington Beach, where 
investigators believe the victim lived. Her identification was withheld pending 
notification of family members. 
</P>
<P>
 A nurse who spotted the vehicle blocking the entrance told a security guard to 
move it because she didn't see "anyone going in or coming out," said Anne 
Warde, hospital marketing specialist. 
</P>
<P>
 The guard "drove it to a parking lot, then found the body while searching for 
some kind of an identification," Warde said. "He had been driving with the dead 
body right beside him and didn't know it." 
</P>
<P>
 Anyone with information should call Irvine police at (714) 724-7011 or (714) 
724-7174. 
</P>
</TEXT>
