<HEADLINE>
<P>
UC IRVINE GALLERY NAMES NEW CURATOR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CATHY CURTIS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Pamela Bailey, 31, has been named curator of the UC Irvine Fine Arts Gallery, 
effective this week.She replaces Mara Lonner, who has left to teach at CalArts 
in Santa Clarita and to spend more time on her own art. 
</P>
<P>
 Bailey formerly was gallery coordinator of Works, a nonprofit institution in 
San Jose. Before that, she worked in the publications department of the J. Paul 
Getty Museum in Malibu, was administrative director of the Fellows of 
Contemporary Art in Los Angeles and interned in the curatorial department of 
the Santa Monica Museum. CATHY CURTIS 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Appointment 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA120994-0336 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 106627 </DOCID>
<SOURCE>
<P>
 Los Angeles Times 
</P>
</SOURCE>
<DATE>
<P>
