<TEXT>
<P>
 Mutual fund holdings -- A chart in Thursday's editions listed certain mutual 
funds' holdings of the debt of all Orange County cities and agencies, not just 
bonds of the county itself.Very little -- if any -- of the non-county debt is 
affected by Orange County's filing for bankruptcy protection. Generally, such 
debt is insured or backed in some other way. The figures are as much as 10 
months old, so the funds' holdings may have changed. The USAA Tax-Exempt 
Short-Term Fund, for example, no longer holds any such debt. 
</P>
</TEXT>
